law.catch_line: Annual report of board -- Principal office -- Register.

text.section: On June 30 of each year the board shall submit to the Governor a written report including the names of all persons to whom licenses have been granted as provided in this chapter and any cases heard and decisions rendered.
The board may locate its principal office, meet, or conduct any of its business at any place in this state.

The board shall keep a record of its proceedings and a register of licensed and certified psychologists, licensed psychological practitioners, and licensed psychological associates. The books and records of the board shall be prima facie evidence of the matters therein contained.

law.history: Amended 2001 Ky. Acts ch. 80, sec. 5, effective June 21, 2001. -- Amended 1988 Ky. Acts ch. 291, sec. 2, effective July 15, 1988. -- Amended 1986 Ky. Acts ch. 128, sec. 5, effective July 15, 1986. -- Amended 1964 Ky. Acts ch. 154, sec. 3. -- Created 1948 Ky. Acts ch. 169, sec. 3.
